         <div type="translation" source="#adams1994" xml:lang="en">
            <p>To Catullus, the <hi rend="italic">agens</hi>, Aemilius Flamininus <hi rend="italic">vice principalis</hi> (sends greetings). You should
               know, lord, that there came to my men the deserter Aban the barbarian on 11 February. I have
               sent you by M. . .</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" resp="#cmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><note>i</note>:  . . . ] donkeys [ . . . ] consuls [ . . . </p>
            <p><note>ii</note>: Aemilius Flamininus lieutenant principalis, to Catulus, agent, You should know, Sir, that a barbarian, Aban, came over as a refugee to 
               my <supplied reason="subaudible">men</supplied> on the third <supplied reason="explanation">day before the</supplied> ides of February. I have sent him to you by M[- . . .] both [ . . . </p>
         </div>

         <div type="commentary" subtype="general">
            <p>11 February? (?).</p>
         </div>
         
